      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "React:\n\nReact is a JavaScrpit Library to build user interfaces(UI) for single page application\n\nReact Features:\n\n\nJSX Rules:\n\n1. JSX can return only 1 element(Parent)\n    so, we need to wrap all elements into one element\n2. Each Tag must be closed !...\n3. We can't use if-else for loops jsu we can use ternery operators & map\n4. Instead of Class(keyword) we need to use ClassName\n5. Instead of for(keyword) we need to use htmlFor \n\n                                      ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "React:\n\nReact is a JavaScrpit Library to build user interfaces(UI) for single page application\n\nReact Features:\n\n\nJSX Rules:\n\n1. JSX can return only 1 element(Parent)\n    so, we need to wrap all elements into one element\n2. Each Tag must be closed !...\n3. We can't use if-else for loops jsu we can use ternery operators & map\n4. Instead of Class(keyword) we need to use ClassName\n5. Instead of for(keyword) we need to use htmlFor \n\n                                      ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
