      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "State:\n\nstate is normal js object which is responsible to hold the data,\nand update it a/c to changes\n\nfunctional based components are stateless component \n\nIf we want to make functional based component as statefull component\nwe nedd to use hook -> useState()\n\nuseState()\n\nuseState is react hook returns 1 array which contains 2 elements inside it\n\n1 is state\n2 is setState - update the function to update that state\n\nsyntax:\n[state,setstate] = useState()\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "State:\n\nstate is normal js object which is responsible to hold the data,\nand update it a/c to changes\n\nfunctional based components are stateless component \n\nIf we want to make functional based component as statefull component\nwe nedd to use hook -> useState()\n\nuseState()\n\nuseState is react hook returns 1 array which contains 2 elements inside it\n\n1 is state\n2 is setState - update the function to update that state\n\nsyntax:\n[state,setstate] = useState()\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
